Take 1 ounce each of wax, black pitch and colophony, 2 ounces each of elemi gum and turpentine, Â½ ounce each of mastic and sarcocol gum, 3 drams each of rock rose gum and eyebright, 5 drams of myrrh and 3 ounces of rose oil. Put all these things in the pot and with a slow fire compound them well, stirring continuously with the spatula so that they do not stick. When they are well cooked in the usual way, remove them from the fire and continue in the usual way for plasters and it will be done. Preserve the powder for your needs and it will bring you honor.

Unguent to cool and heal every sore.

